FBIS3-36525 "drsov025_b_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Makes Counterintelligence Appointments LD0402203594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1752 GMT 4 Feb 94 LD0402203594 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin appointed by decree on Friday General-Lieutenants Andrey Bykov, Aleksandr Strelkov and Valeriy Timofeyev as deputies director of the Russian Counter-Intelligence Service, the presidential press service reports. Lieutenant-Colonel Aleksandr Mikhailov was appointed as the Chief of the Public Relations Center.
